news.title: Unregistered homestays must complete registration: Kodagu DC
news.para: During a meeting with district hospitality sector representatives, he discussed tourist safety measures. He highlighted the simplified homestay registration process, noting quick document verification and certificate issuance.

news.title: Madurai’s ageing housing complexes raise safety concerns
news.para: The decades-old structures at Race Course Colony, Chokkikulam, DRO Colony, and Pykara—built between 1964 and 1987—are crumbling due to poor maintenance, forcing many residents to vacate.

news.title: Kerala government urges centre to drop PMAY branding mandate
news.para: ​Local self-govt and excise minister MB Rajesh raised this concern during a meeting with Union housing and urban affairs minister Manohar Lal Khattar. Rajesh argued that the branding requirement affects beneficiaries' dignity and self-respect.

news.title: Karnataka: Supply power to only buildings with OCs, KERC tells Bescom
news.para: In its Dec 17, 2024 judgment, Supreme Court had also mandated that completion certificates be issued to new buildings only if the sanctioned plan is adhered to and violations, if any, are rectified.

news.title: Odisha court orders disbursement of Rs 450 crore to investors of scam-hit Rose Valley group
news.para: ​The special PMLA court in Bhubaneswar has ordered the release of Rs 332.76 crore of proceeds of crime, whose present value is Rs 450 crore with interest, the Enforcement Department (ED) said in a statement.

news.title: Four more cases lodged against Ansal Properties and Infrastructure
news.para: The cases involve allegations of financial deception, fraudulent property transfers, and intimidation tactics against complainants.

news.title: Nashik civic body's chief asks smart city corporation to complete projects soon
news.para: Official of NMSCDCL, during the meeting with Khatri, gave a presentation about the projects that were taken under the Smart City mission and also the projects completed and the ones under construction.

news.title: HC directs YEIDA to take over and finish Jaypee projects on SDZ land
news.para: JAL launched 12 housing projects here, which have around 4,600 investors. Another 13 were launched by other developers on land that was sub-leased to them by JAL. YEIDA had cancelled the allotment on Feb 12, 2020, citing JAL's dues.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC seeks proof of subsidiary status of two firms from Bhopal collector
news.para: The court asked Verma to produce the stay order in the court within 24 hours. The apex court, in its order, stayed the RERA order for recovery from M/s Unitech Ltd and its subsidiary companies.

news.title: NCLT approves scheme of arrangement between Dalmia Bharat's subsidiaries
news.para: The Scheme, which comes into effect from the appointed date of March 31, 2023, was sanctioned under Sections 230 to 232 of the Companies Act, 2013.

news.title: Chandigarh administration may hike property tax for FY26
news.para: A special committee, headed by the UT finance secretary, has determined that the city's current property tax, calculated at 3% of annual ratable value, is lower compared to neighbouring and other major cities.

news.title: Chandigarh administration issues fresh guidelines for demolition of illegal structures
news.para: The DC office must also designate a nodal officer to communicate the information of demolition to relevant authorities, mentioning the specific violations while issuing demolition orders.

news.title: UBS considers sale of some real estate assets in Switzerland: Sources
news.para: The business area under review includes mainly Swiss real estate assets and, according to one of the people who declined to be named because the matter is private, could be worth less than $1 billion.

news.title: UK's Savills expects employees' return-to-office to boost real estate
news.para: Savills has been grappling with weakness in China and delays to some transactions in North America, while bond market turbulence earlier this year dented investor sentiment.

news.title: Blackstone to buy 40% stake in Kolte-Patil Developers for $134 million
news.para: Kolte-Patil will allot a Blackstone entity 14.3% preferential shares in a deal worth 4.17 billion rupees, while its controlling shareholders will sell another 25.7% to the U.S. firm for about 7.5 billion rupees.

news.title: Topsoe leases 75,000 sq ft office space from Table Space in Noida
news.para: The company is a global leader in developing technologies that drive the energy transition, supporting industries in achieving sustainability and carbon reduction goals.

news.title: Raipur's Dantewada district digitizes over seven lakh land records
news.para: Blockchain technology, known for its security and resistance to tampering, is increasingly being adopted across various sectors, including land record management.

news.title: Jammu & Kashmir government identifies 625 acres of land for industrial estates
news.para: The government has granted 36 limestone mining leases, 24 gypsum mining leases, and 202 e-auctioned minor mineral blocks, he said.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh's 2025-26 budget prioritizes urban development with major allocations
news.para: Urban transformation programmes receive notable attention, with Rs 1,071 crore allocated to AMRUT 2.0 and Rs 1,000 crore to Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Urban) 2.0 BLC.

news.title: Bihar government extends deadline for land survey till December 2026
news.para: "The department has decided to extend the July 2026 deadline for the completion of the ongoing work of the survey and settlement of lands across the state by five months
